parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion of Radius Arm Brackets, Cross Members, and Brake Lines
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of these components can lead to a loss of vehicle control, increased stopping distance, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit corrosion on the radius arm brackets
cross members
and brake lines
which can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor
making it difficult or impossible to shift gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure due to ABS System Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the ABS system can cause the brakes to fail, leading to extended stopping distances, loss of vehicle control, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The brakes may fail to function properly
especially on wet or uneven surfaces
causing the vehicle to take longer to stop or lose control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the ABS system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances, loss of vehicle control, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The ABS system may malfunction intermittently
causing the brakes to fail or the pedal to travel to the floor
especially on wet or uneven surfaces.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Oil Pump Shell Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil pump shell can cause the engine to seize, leading to costly repairs and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine makes a knocking sound
the engine seizes
the vehicle stalls
the oil pump shell fails
the crank and block are destroyed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing belt can cause the engine to stall, leading to costly repairs and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The timing belt breaks
the engine stalls
the vehicle dies
the timing belt is in shreds
the vehicle is unable to restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling fan assembly can cause the engine to overheat, leading to costly repairs and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The cooling fan assembly falls off
the cooling fan support breaks
the fan belt tears
the aluminum housing cracks and breaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various issues, including faulty switches, dimming lights, and inaccurate gas gauge readings, which can lead to safety concerns and inconvenience.
symptoms: Switches do not work or stop working
interior lights dim
the gas gauge gives false readings
the dome light stays on
the stereo light does not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission and clutch can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to costly repairs and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle decelerates without warning
the clutch blows out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the head gasket can cause the engine to overheat, leading to costly repairs and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The head gasket fails
the engine overheats
the vehicle loses radiator fluid.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Crankshaft Pulley and Water Pump Pulley Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft pulley and water pump pulley can cause the engine to overheat, leading to costly repairs and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The crankshaft pulley and water pump pulley fall off
the engine overheats.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An inaccurate fuel gauge can lead to unexpected fuel depletion, causing the vehicle to stall or run out of fuel, which can be dangerous, especially when driving on highways or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The fuel gauge reads full until the tank is nearly empty
then drops suddenly; the fuel gauge registers full until the tank is at 1/2
then runs out of gas at 1/8 to 1/4 showing on the gauge; the fuel gauge reads full until the tank is approximately 1/2 empty
then reads 1/4 tank on the gauge.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel leaks can cause fuel spillage, which can lead to fires, explosions, or other accidents, and can also cause the vehicle to stall or run out of fuel.
symptoms: Fuel injection leaks
fuel spillage
hissing noise from the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause loss of power steering, making it difficult to control the vehicle, especially when slowing down or turning, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls when slowing down at stops or while slowing down to make turns
power steering is impossible
hissing noise from the engine.
